## 3. Key Domain Concepts

### ReportPortal Launch
- A test execution run; contains metadata: CNV version, OCP version, tier, bundle, cluster name
- Stats: total, passed, failed, skipped
- Status values: PASSED, FAILED, INTERRUPTED, STOPPED, IN_PROGRESS

### Test Item
- Individual test case within a launch; failed items include error message, defect type, Polarion ID
- Can be linked to Jira issues and classified with defect types

### Defect Classification
- RP defect types: Product Bug, Automation Bug, System Issue, To Investigate, No Defect
- Triage from dashboard updates classification in ReportPortal

### Daily Report
- Groups launches by CNV version and tier; computes pass rates, identifies new vs recurring failures

### Acknowledgment
- QE signs off that they reviewed the daily report; tracked per date and reviewer

