## 6. Configuration

All configuration via environment variables (see `packages/server/src/config.ts`):

| Variable | Purpose | Default |
|----------|---------|---------|
| `REPORTPORTAL_URL` | RP API base URL | (internal Red Hat URL) |
| `REPORTPORTAL_TOKEN` | RP auth token | (required) |
| `REPORTPORTAL_PROJECT` | RP project name | CNV |
| `SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL` | Slack incoming webhook | (disabled if empty) |
| `SMTP_HOST`, `SMTP_PORT`, etc. | Email config | (disabled if empty) |
| `JIRA_URL`, `JIRA_TOKEN` | Jira config | (disabled if empty) |
| `CRON_SCHEDULE` | Poll schedule | `0 7 * * *` |
| `DASHBOARD_PORT` | Server port | 8080 |
| `DB_PATH` | SQLite file location | `./data/monitor.db` |

---

## 7. Data Flow

```
K8s CronJob (7 AM) → pollReportPortal() → ReportPortal API
                         ↓
                   SQLite (launches, test_items)
                         ↓
                   buildDailyReport() → Slack + Email

K8s Deployment → Express → serves React SPA + REST API
                   ↓
         React (TanStack Query) → /api/* → SQLite + RP + Jira
```

---

## 8. Development

```bash
npm install                   # Install all workspaces
npm run dev                   # Concurrently: server (8080) + client (5173 with proxy)
npm run dev:server            # Server only
npm run dev:client            # Client only (Vite)
npm run build                 # Build shared → server → client
npm run typecheck             # TypeScript check (shared + server)
npm run test                  # Vitest (server)
npm run poll                  # Run one poll cycle
```

---

## 9. Deployment

### Docker (multi-stage monorepo build)
```bash
podman build -t quay.io/openshift-cnv/cnv-ui-monitor:latest .
```

### Kubernetes
```bash
kubectl apply -f k8s/ -n cnv-monitor
```

### CI
GitHub Actions: build all packages → typecheck → test → build Docker → push to Quay.io
